        <briefdescription>
<para>Detection probability for given per-sample amplitude SNR and dwell. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Computes Pd = Q_1(a, eta) where a = sqrt(2 * dwell) * snr.</para>
<para>At snr = 0, det_pd returns Pfa (the false-alarm rate, as expected for a noise-only input). As snr or dwell increase, Pd approaches 1.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>snr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Per-sample amplitude SNR (signal / noise amplitude, linear). snr = 0 gives Pd = Pfa. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dwell</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Coherent integration depth; must be &gt;= 1. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>threshold</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Test-stat threshold eta, e.g. from <ref refid="detection__core_8h_1aea1ad6723d6546157611a21518e35e35" kindref="member">det_threshold()</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Detection probability in &amp;#91;0, 1&amp;#93;.</para>
</simplesect>
Example: det_pd(1.0, 4, det_threshold(1e-6)) ~ 0.78 </para>
        </detaileddescription>
